    <title>npm version manager</title>
    <link href="http://lancegin.cc/tech/npm-version-manager/"/>
    <id>http://lancegin.cc/tech/npm-version-manager/</id>
    <published>2016-11-07T08:27:31.000Z</published>
    <updated>2017-08-27T13:04:36.000Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Haven’t writen node for a long time, the version on my mac is still 5.x, today I find a easy way to update node to the latest version.</p>
<p><code>node</code> has a self module called <code>n</code>, it is really called <code>n</code> 2333…You can easily install it to the globle environment by :</p>
<figure class="highlight shell"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><div class="line">1</div></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><div class="line">npm install -g n</div></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<p><code>n</code> for node is just like <code>rvm</code> for ruby, it can manage the version of node conveniently, so you can update node to the latest stable version by :</p>
<figure class="highlight shell"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><div class="line">1</div></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><div class="line">n stable</div></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<p>then it will be successful.</p>
<p>But it is not the end, after you update node to the latest version, the <code>npm</code> will have an error <code>Error: Cannot find module &#39;internal/fs&#39;</code>, that’s because the version of npm hasn’t been the newest, so the direct way to fix it is UPDATING npm by <code>npm -g install npm@next</code>, but it will still render a same error. Now you should change the node version to <code>6.x</code> by:</p>
<figure class="highlight shell"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><div class="line">1</div></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><div class="line">n [ version ]</div></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<p>then you can update the npm by:</p>
<figure class="highlight shell"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><div class="line">1</div></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><div class="line">npm -g install npm@next</div></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<p>now you can change the node version to the latest stable. </p>
<p>and it will be fine.</p>
]]></content>
    
