    <title>Install Package Control in ST3</title>
    <link href="http://lancegin.cc/tech/Install-Package-Control-in-ST3/"/>
    <id>http://lancegin.cc/tech/Install-Package-Control-in-ST3/</id>
    <published>2015-11-01T08:27:31.000Z</published>
    <updated>2017-08-27T05:42:34.000Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>ST (Sublime Text) is a very sexy IDE for me while coding, but if you update it to ST3, you will found that some packages could not be installed. It is just because sublime has update Python to the latest version, so we should reinstall the Package Control Tool.</p>
<p>• first you can tap <code>ctrl + ~</code> to open the console window and copy the python codes below to it, then tap <code>Enter</code>.</p>
<figure class="highlight python"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><div class="line">1</div><div class="line">2</div><div class="line">3</div><div class="line">4</div><div class="line">5</div><div class="line">6</div></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><div class="line"><span class="keyword">import</span> urllib.request</div><div class="line"><span class="keyword">import</span> os</div><div class="line">pf = <span class="string">'Package Control.sublime-package'</span></div><div class="line">ipp = sublime.installed_packages_path()</div><div class="line">urllib.request.install_opener( urllib.request.build_opener( urllib.request.ProxyHandler()) )</div><div class="line">open(os.path.join(ipp, pf), <span class="string">'wb'</span>).write(urllib.request.urlopen( <span class="string">'http://sublime.wbond.net/'</span> + pf.replace(<span class="string">' '</span>,<span class="string">'%20'</span>)).read())</div></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
<p>• the console window will show a note such as “a missing dependency was just installed” if successfull.</p>
<p><img src="http://outub9z8v.bkt.clouddn.com/package_control_01.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p>• now you can install the packages you want by tapping <code>Command + Shift + P</code> then input <code>install</code>.</p>
<p><img src="http://outub9z8v.bkt.clouddn.com/package_control_02.jpg" alt=""></p>
]]></content>
    
