    <title>Use Manifest to Add Resources to Local Cache</title>
    <link href="http://lancegin.cc/tech/Use-Manifest-to-Add-Resources-to-Local-Cache/"/>
    <id>http://lancegin.cc/tech/Use-Manifest-to-Add-Resources-to-Local-Cache/</id>
    <published>2015-10-27T09:27:31.000Z</published>
    <updated>2017-08-27T05:14:13.000Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>When we develop the HTML5 web app, we can use manifest file to reduce the loading time of some resources. It’s a test project about <code>manifest</code> below to show the effect.</p>
<p>• when the website load at the first time, we’ll see all the resources were loaded from network.</p>
<p><img src="http://outub9z8v.bkt.clouddn.com/manifest_01.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p>• if we click to another page and go back to this page, all the resouces we need will be loaded from cache.</p>
<p><img src="http://outub9z8v.bkt.clouddn.com/manifest_02.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p>• but if we refresh the current page, all the resouces will be loaded from network again, it will waste much time if th resouces are large.</p>
<p><img src="http://outub9z8v.bkt.clouddn.com/manifest_03.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p>If we use manifest file, we can easily solve this problem.</p>
<p>• at first link your mnifest file at the head of your <code>html file</code></p>
<p><img src="http://outub9z8v.bkt.clouddn.com/manifest_04.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p>• then config your manifest file to choose the resources you want to be loaded from cache</p>
<p><img src="http://outub9z8v.bkt.clouddn.com/manifest_05.jpg" alt=""></p>
<ol>
<li>CACHE MANIFEST` is necessary</li>
<li>the file under <code>CACHE</code> will be loaded from cache.</li>
<li>the file under <code>NETWORK</code> will be loaded from network.</li>
<li>if the resource could not be found, <code>404.html</code> will be loaded.</li>
</ol>
<p>• then you can refresh your website, you’ll found the resources you want to be loaded from cache were loaded from cache.</p>
<p><img src="http://outub9z8v.bkt.clouddn.com/manifest_06.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p>Your website will be refreshed in a high speed in this way.</p>
]]></content>
    
