    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>When I used Rubygems to install some application times ago, I usually meet the problem that says “connection error”.</p>
<p>Today when I tapped <code>sudo gem install rails</code>, I met the problem again, just like the pic below.</p>
<p><img src="http://outub9z8v.bkt.clouddn.com/rubygem_01.png" alt=""></p>
<p>Now I introduce an easy way to solve this problem.</p>
<p>• use <code>gem sources</code> to list the sources you have used. You will see the source <code>https://rubygems.org/</code></p>
<p><img src="http://outub9z8v.bkt.clouddn.com/rubygem_02.png" alt=""></p>
<p>• use <code>gem sources -a http://rubygems.org</code> to add the new source with “http”</p>
<p><img src="http://outub9z8v.bkt.clouddn.com/rubygem_03.png" alt=""></p>
<p>• use <code>gem sources -r https://rubygem.org/</code> to remove the old source with “https”</p>
<p><img src="http://outub9z8v.bkt.clouddn.com/rubygem_04.png" alt=""></p>
<p>• then you will not have the connection problem.</p>
<p><img src="http://outub9z8v.bkt.clouddn.com/rubygem_05.png" alt=""></p>
<p>• If you still have some problem when you use <code>bundle</code>, you can use <code>gem sources -a http://ruby.taobao.org</code> to add taobao ruby to your source.</p>
]]></content>
    
