    <title>Better iTerm</title>
    <link href="http://lancegin.cc/tech/better-iTerm/"/>
    <id>http://lancegin.cc/tech/better-iTerm/</id>
    <published>2015-04-25T08:27:00.000Z</published>
    <updated>2017-08-27T05:13:17.000Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="Useful-Guide-about-Iterm-and-Zsh"><a href="#Useful-Guide-about-Iterm-and-Zsh" class="headerlink" title="Useful Guide about Iterm and Zsh"></a>Useful Guide about Iterm and Zsh</h1><blockquote>
<p>in this article, I will set an very easy Iterm, the plugins I will use are very covenient for us to use the Iterm, Vim ,and Terminal.</p>
</blockquote>
<h3 id="Dowload-Iterm"><a href="#Dowload-Iterm" class="headerlink" title="Dowload Iterm"></a>Dowload Iterm</h3><p>click <a href="http://iterm2.com/downloads.html" target="_blank" rel="external">iterm2.com</a> to download the latest version.</p>
<h3 id="Install-Zsh"><a href="#Install-Zsh" class="headerlink" title="Install Zsh"></a>Install Zsh</h3><h4 id="1-via-curl"><a href="#1-via-curl" class="headerlink" title="1. via curl"></a>1. via curl</h4><p><code>curl -L https://raw.github.com/robbyrussell/oh-my-zsh/master/tools/install.sh | sh</code></p>
<h4 id="2-via-wget"><a href="#2-via-wget" class="headerlink" title="2. via wget"></a>2. via wget</h4><p><code>wget https://raw.github.com/robbyrussell/oh-my-zsh/master/tools/install.sh -O - | sh</code></p>
<h4 id="3-manual-installation"><a href="#3-manual-installation" class="headerlink" title="3. manual installation"></a>3. manual installation</h4><p>. clone the repository:</p>
<p><code>git clone git://github.com/robbyrussell/oh-my-zsh.git ~/.oh-my-zsh</code></p>
<p>. backup your ~./zshrc file</p>
<p><code>cp ~/.zshrc ~/.zshrc.orig</code></p>
<p>. creat your new configuration file</p>
<p><code>cp ~/.oh-my-zsh/templates/zshrc.zsh-template ~/.zshrc</code></p>
<p>. change your default shell</p>
<p><code>chsh -s /bin/zsh</code></p>
<blockquote>
<p>now you have finish installing your new toys–iTerm2 and oh-my-zsh. You can just have a try.</p>
</blockquote>
<h3 id="Font-Setting"><a href="#Font-Setting" class="headerlink" title="Font Setting"></a>Font Setting</h3><ol>
<li>open your iTerm2, and open the <code>Profiles</code> or press <code>command + O</code></li>
<li>select your loving font.</li>
</ol>
<h3 id="Blendent"><a href="#Blendent" class="headerlink" title="Blendent"></a>Blendent</h3><p>if you use iTerm2 on Mac, you will find that the default blendent is very ugly. I can’t stand it.</p>
<p>so taday I will recommend a very beautiful color blendent <code>Solarized</code></p>
<p>like this shot below</p>
<p><img src="http://outub9z8v.bkt.clouddn.com/1.png" alt=""></p>
<ol>
<li>download Salarized</li>
</ol>
<p><code>git clone git://github.com/altercation/solarized.git</code></p>
<ol>
<li>add the color blendent to your iterm2</li>
</ol>
<p>open the folder you downloaded just now, then select the folder <code>iTerm2-colors-solarized</code>, double click the <code>.itermcolor</code> file, now you can open your <code>Profiles</code> to select your new blendent.</p>
<p>  now, I found another beautiful blendent named “tomorrow”,you can download it via <code>git clone git:github.com/chriskempson/tomorrow-theme</code>, then goto step 2 above.</p>
<h3 id="Theme"><a href="#Theme" class="headerlink" title="Theme"></a>Theme</h3><p>. <code>oh-my-zsh</code> has provided many kinds of <a href="https://github.com/robbyrussell/oh-my-zsh/wiki/Themes" target="_blank" rel="external">Themes</a>, choose the best one you like.</p>
<p>. open your <code>.zshrc</code> file</p>
<p><code>vi ~/.zshrc</code></p>
<p>. find <code>ZSH_THEME=&quot;agnoster&quot;</code>, and change the theme name.</p>
<p>. reopen iTerm2.</p>
<h3 id="Plugins"><a href="#Plugins" class="headerlink" title="Plugins"></a>Plugins</h3><p>. <a href="https://github.com/joelthelion/autojump" target="_blank" rel="external">autojump</a> is a very nice plugin.</p>
<h3 id="More-is-Coming…"><a href="#More-is-Coming…" class="headerlink" title="More is Coming…"></a>More is Coming…</h3><blockquote>
<p>If you have any suggestions, you can push them to me, I will read them carefully!</p>
</blockquote>
